<h3 id="clicktarget">Clicktarget</h3>
<div class="grid-2">
  <p><img src="../images/components/radio-buttons/radiobutton-clicktarget.svg" alt="Illustration of the extent of the clicktarget of a Checkbox." /></p>

  <div>
    <p>A radio button can be selected by clicking on the area of its indicator as well as its label. Usually the clicktarget extends to the same width for each element in a collection of radio buttons. This results in a click target that extends beyond the label, for all elements shorter than the longest.</p>

    <p>Clicking a radio button selects it on release of the click. If, during the click, the mouse is moved off of the radio button, it does not become selected.</p>
  </div>
</div>

